How evolved the prices of trips since 1989
Until 1989 there were in Czechoslovakia only 5 state travel agencies: Cedok, Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autotourist.
Travel agencies in this epoch offered trips especially in the countries of the socialist block, because trips on the West were very limited.
The Czech tourists travelled for holiday in East Germany, Soviet Union (Sotchi, Crimea and Black Sea), in Bulgaria, Romania (two in Black Sea) and in Hungary (Balaton).
A big exception for period from 1962 till 1972 when he was authorised to travel in Yugoslavia then regime began having an inclination as the west and trips towards Yugoslavia were very limited for the Czech tourists.
The big paradox of socialist epoch was that it nétait not allowed for the citizens of the socialist block (also for the Czechoslovakian) to travel individually even as part of the socialist countries.
In case the Czechoslovakian citizen wanted to travel individually for example in Poland or in Soviet Union he needed a letter of invitation otherwise individual trip wasn't allowed.
Travel agencies in this epoch also gave trips on the West however it was necessary to queue up all night with a sleeping bag or to have "good knowledge" within the travel agency.
And even thereafter it wasn't earned yet.
The agreement for the currencies which was condition to travel on the West was refused politically wrong "people" who could travel in no way.
The Czechoslovakian currency wasn't however exchangeable and it wasn't possible to get medium financiers without the agreement of currencies (Western currency) to travel on the West.
The Czechs spent their holiday most often in the country where there were as a result many villas and chalets which the Czechs bought and this hard habit up to now.
Trips of the Czechs since knew since 1989 a big revolution.
