But footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a magnifier galtonienne, of some ink, a préleveur and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those of the card.
The eye deceived him not: it was of '"Alfonso Cano".
The same night, the man native to Puerto Tejada was the representative who confirmed to the minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, it was about the commander in chief of Farc.
In search of footprint
For a dactyloscopiste of Sijín of Cali the recognition that the president Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, in a press conference for operation against "Cano", am very significant.
Many people of connait not our job.
The dactyloscopie is a precise science, without margin of error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
Apart to identify bodies, dactyloscopistes supports investigations for offences as flight and the homicide and confirms the identity of the captured persons.
When are captured, many delinquents introduce wrong identity cards or don't have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in database.
The researcher narrated that in a case of flight he had to take away a part of wall of a home, because in this place the thief had supported the hand to get outside a safe full of jewellery and money.
"Walls are difficult because they aren't adequate areas to draw fingerprints, but in that case we could get the footprint of all hand and identify with the delinquent who had participated in different flights", he remembers.
Footprints can also move aside or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently a dead man, with bottles of drink around him was found.
By interlude of investigation they determined that a parent can be suspicious of crime and indeed a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it no guarantees not that he is the murderer, it puts him on the stage of crime.
A dactyloscopiste of CTI explained that they extract "the fingerprints of objects with one reactive chemical or physical".
When they appear, a préleveur or a band are used to take a sample of them.
Subsequently, footprints are sent to Asif, the database of déclinquents, or to the National Civil Register.
"Problem is that there are some more Colombians without papers", pointed out the expert of the CTI.
He explained that everything isn't how they show in TV programme CSI.
As all that shines isn't gold, everything that is touched forcing doesn't become a footprint.
She can however be used, if necessary confrontation is accomplished.
