Russia could, in five years barely, make triumph its vision of a direct alliance between Russia and rich Western, strongly consumer countries of gas, and deposits of which are in decline.
" This gas pipeline is an element of our partnership with Russia, it is a new artery which links us in an organic way", confirmed François Fillon by inaugurating this gas pipeline, showing to what extent the big gas contracts are as political as economic.
All that explains broad grins shown by the leaders of Gazprom, gifts in numbers in Lubmin, so as to arrival of the gas.
The building of this gas pipeline is also a technical feat.
The underwater tube is steel sheathed by concrete to protect it against the anchors of ships.
He is based on the bottom of the sea, in 200 m on average.
To construct it, it was necessary to avoid minefields dating from World War II.
" A hundred must be taken away or destroyed, by precaution", points out Jens Müller, spokesperson of the North society Stream.
It was also necessary to multiply measures to protect fauna and flora.
The tube is a long metal snake, heavy as 242 turns Eiffel, whom nothing interrupts on all its length: neither valve, or station of service.
A deck of control was envisaged off Sweden, but the representatives for plan abandoned it while the Swedes were not very eager to see a society of Russian State settling permanently off the coasts.
" In case of damage, we stop the passage of the gas in less than one minute", specifies Jens Müller.
In case of escape, the gas contained in the gas pipeline escapes therefore in air.
But this case is considered unlikely by the constructors who envisaged soldering to know an escape every 100 000 years.
The surveillance of the state of the gas pipeline is assured by an underwater robot, dragged by a ship, for external observation, as well as by an apparatus which circulates inside the gas pipeline.
In the form of a cigar, he is introduced inside the tube, one metre broad in diameter, and he is pushed by the gas.
At arrival, after three complete days of trip at the speed of 3 metres back up, it delivers definite information on possible distortions of the metal.
The gas pipeline was conceived to work fifty years without credit to suffer the slightest repairing.
The circulation of the gas is simply assured by pressure.
It is 200 bars at first, and 100 at arrival.
Five societies joined their force to accomplish this plan.
The leader remains Gazprom, who keeps 51 % of parts.
E.ON and BASF joined it German (15,5 % each), as well as Dutch Gasunie and the French GDF group Sweat (9 % each).
These five societies created a North common, called firm Stream, made responsible for constructing and for operating on the gas pipeline.
She has her seat in Zoug, in Switzerland, where the taxation is particularly favourable.
Gazprom then rented to this society, for twenty renewable years, the totality of the capacities of transport of gas.
" Gazprom will pay for the complete capacity, whatever is the quantity of gas indeed transported", specifies Jens Müller.
The financing of the building of the gas pipeline was assured 30 % by the shareholders and 70 % by banking loans.
The total cost of jobs should attain 7,4 thousand million euro for both tubes.
For GDF Sweat the investment, for example, came to 240 millions.
But the minority shareholders are sure of coming back into their expenses, since only Gazprom takes risk.
The gas pipeline appears from the Baltic Sea to Lubmin, on sandy coastal region planted of pines.
Valves, 4,5 metres high, form the exit of the gas.
Sensors measure pressure, temperature and specificity of the gas which arrives, before it is transferred in the German gas pipelines.
Since last Tuesday, this terminal receives a million cubic metres of Russian gas every hour which passes.
In full capacity, these will be 3 millions an hour and in 2012, 6 millions.
