In spite of a voluntarist public policy set up in 2005, unemployment rate of the handicapped persons is still twice as high as average: 19 %, against 9 % for the whole population.
Discouraging?
" No, underlines Éric Blanchet, managing director of Adapt, the association which organises the week for the job of the disabled persons."
" Progress fulfilled for fifteen years is considerable."
" At that time the unemployment rate wasn't two but three times as high."
" It remains still tremendously nevertheless to make."
It is necessary to say that for the handicapped unemployed persons, obstacles remain many before achieving job.
They are rather old: 37 % are more than 50 years old (17 % on average).
They have a not very high qualification level: 80 % have no receptacle and on 2,3 million students of higher education, 10 000 only are handicapped.
Finally, the long-term unemployment is very spread: 53 % for the disabled persons, against 38 % on average.
In short, so much criteria which complicate particularly the return to job, and that "constitute the knot of problem", according to Christian Grapin, managing director of Ski jump, an association created in 1992 to help firms to recruit handicapped workers.
Here is for the objective brakes.
The unsaid, the mentalities stays which evolve, certainly, but too slowly.
A study accomplished in April by the association IMS-ENTREPRENDRE for the City pointed out that the questioned managers have "a level of weak knowledge of disability", with a "overrepresentation of the persons in wheelchair, of deficient psychical or intellectual".
Result, the private business of more than 20 wage earners is still far from reaching the target of job of 6 % of handicapped workers, fixed in a law of... On 1987.
The last known figures, which date of 2008, mention a 2,6 % ratio.
" We are now around 3 %", points out Pierre Blanc, managing director of Agefiph, organism made responsible for collecting the contributions of the firms which don't respect this law.
Proof: the number of establishments "taxed ", just as poured sums, diminished between 2007 and 2011, passing 59 000 - 46 000 structures (and from 606 to 480 millions of euro).
" The law of 2005, which augmented contributions, created a strong pressure on firms, explains Pierre Blanc."
" But this improvement also translates a true realisation, especially in the big groups."
According to the ministry of job, only 59 % of establishments 20 - 49 wage earners use handicapped workers, against 82 % of firms 100 - 199 wage earners.
